  <subsection>
            <title>Summary</title>
            <p><ul>
                <li>
                    <p>An <term>enhanced for loop</term>, also called a <term>for each loop</term>, can be used to loop through an array without using an index variable.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>An enhanced for loop header includes a variable, referred to as the enhanced for loop variable, that holds each value in the array.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>For each iteration of the enhanced for loop, the enhanced for loop variable is assigned a copy of an element without using its index.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Assigning a new value to the enhanced for loop variable does not change the value stored in the array.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Program code written using an enhanced for loop to traverse and access elements in an array can be rewritten using an indexed for loop or a while loop.</p>
                </li>
            </ul></p>
